In a word: Yes. When you remove the tap-hold logic from a key, it becomes instantaneous.

Why it feels "Crisper"
Currently, when you press your Left Alt, Kanata has to wait for one of two things to happen before it sends a signal to your OS:

The hold-time (200ms) expires, at which point it decides "Okay, this is Alt."

You release the key before the timer, at which point it says "Got it, that was Escape."

By making it a dedicated Escape key, the signal is sent the exact millisecond the switch actuates. There is zero processing delay. For a key like Escape—which you often hit with a sense of "get me out of here!"—that 200ms lag is very noticeable.

The "Clean" Modification
Since you already have lalt on your home row (@alt_s), you aren't actually losing the Alt modifier functionality; you're just moving it to the home row exclusively.

